This is a third party issue caused by bugs in IE8 that will cause it to request invalid urls such as:
{quote}
152.91.9.133 - - [14/Sep/2009:01:55:48 -0500] "GET /s/448/1/1.0/_/download/bat%20%20%20%20%20acc=subText%3E%3Cspan%20class=date%3E21/Jun/09%2007:23%20PM%3C/span%3E%3C/span%3E%20%20%3C/div%3E%20%20%20%20%3Cdiv%20class= HTTP/1.1" 404 1081 "http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CWD-86" "Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 8.0; Windows NT 6.0; Trident/4.0; SLCC1; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; .NET CLR 3.0.30729; .NET CLR 1.1.4322; .NET CLR 3.5.30729; InfoPath.2)" 1224
{quote}

The problem is described in more detail here:
* http://blogs.msdn.com/ieinternals/archive/2009/07/27/Bugs-in-the-IE8-Lookahead-Downloader.aspx
* http://connect.microsoft.com/IE/feedback/ViewFeedback.aspx?FeedbackID=467062

There's no ill effects for the end user but it does cause some ugly exceptions in the logs. See attachment for more details.
